Fighting broke out between Palestinianguerrillas and Shi'ite Moslem Amal militiamen near camps insouth lebanon as Syria prepared to extend its military presenceat Beirut's settlements.    Security sources in the southern port of Sidon said theclashes erupted in villages to the southeast between Amal andguerrillas loyal to Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat.    Syria stepped in yesterday to halt battles at two Beirutrefugee camps but Amal said it would only lift its siege afterArafat withdrew his men from the villages near Sidon. Reuter&#3;